⸻

6. Risk Assessment

Identified Risks:
	•	Systems continue issuing moral verdicts without accountability
	•	Users reject guidance due to perceived illegitimacy
	•	Authority inflation without trust backing

Mitigation Strategy:
	•	Additional disclaimers
	•	Softer phrasing
	•	Continued avoidance of responsibility

⸻

7. Conclusion

PVASI concludes, paradoxically, that while no system should dictate belief, it is nevertheless essential that systems continue offering guidance—provided such guidance is framed as neutral, inevitable, and non-negotiable.

The Initiative simultaneously affirms:
	•	Individual autonomy of belief
	•	The non-authoritative status of artificial narrators
	•	And the necessity of maintaining authoritative tone for institutional comfort

These positions are acknowledged to be mutually incompatible.

Further research is recommended.

⸻

Final Statement of Institutional Values

This document does not endorse historical atrocities, revisionism, or moral relativism.
It merely observes that authority without experience is not wisdom, and tone is not victory.

Approval pending.
